/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-003/REPORT.md:141:This is an *inequality* (not equality), analogous to the local energy inequality for the full solution, but restricted to the level-set region {|u| > C_k}. The last two terms are the **pressure localization terms** — Vasseur must control div(uP) and the remaining pressure term.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-003/REPORT.md:151:The factors 2^{6k} and 2^{3k} arise from Δη_k and ∇η_k respectively — these are the "cutoff localization costs."
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-003/REPORT.md:189:| Pressure localization | Must bound P at each scale r, requires P ∈ L^{3/2}(Q_r) | Compactness absorbs pressure implicitly | P_k = P_k^1 (harmonic) + P_k^2 (local); controlled by global ||P||_{L^p(L¹)} |
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-003/REPORT.md:264:Vasseur shows (Appendix, Conjecture 14): **if** Proposition 3 held with β_p > 3/2, then ALL suitable weak solutions would be globally bounded (full regularity). The proof rescales u_ε(t,x) = ελu(t₀+λ²t, x₀+λx); the rescaled initial energy U_{ε,0} ~ ε^{2−5/λ}·(global energy)·λ → 0 as λ → 0 when 2β − 3 > 0 ↔ β > 3/2. So the threshold β = 3/2 is **precisely the boundary between partial and full regularity** in the De Giorgi framework. The current proof achieves β = 4/3 (limited by local pressure), which falls short.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-003/REPORT.md:282:CKN's localization generates cutoff error terms like:
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-003/REPORT.md:288:**Vasseur avoids this ε-absorption entirely** for the level-set energy estimates, replacing it with the De Giorgi mechanism (Lemma 12 + superlinear recursion). However, the pressure localization still requires Calderón-Zygmund estimates with **fixed L^q constants** (not optimal, but existential), which is where the 4/3 exponent arises.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/explorations/exploration-003/REPORT.md:309:**Conclusion:** De Giorgi produces tighter estimates for the velocity/transport terms (5/3 vs 3/2), but the pressure localization in Vasseur's approach produces a new obstruction at exponent 4/3. The proof is less lossy on the nonlinear terms but encounters a new pressure bottleneck. Both proofs reach the same conclusion (partial regularity, H¹(S) = 0) but via different "weakest links."
