/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/selected/chain-01.md:41:- Action: test whether an apparent gain is really pressure-localization nostalgia, near-Beltrami geometry, or another effect better treated in a different branch.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-01.md:23:The attacker is right that exact rewrites of the same quadratic nonlinearity usually collapse back to the same localized costs once projection, commutators, and cutoffs are restored. The refined chain should therefore assume collapse is the baseline outcome unless a sharply identified mechanism defeats it.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-01.md:63:This critique lands cleanly. The original chain does not choose one mission-central bottleneck, one fixed localization protocol, and one bookkeeping currency of gain sharply enough. Without that, derivative reduction, integrability improvement, and closure improvement are not genuinely comparable.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-01.md:71:The attacker is right that "where the localization cost lands" is the whole problem. Two rewrites with the same headline scaling can differ materially in commutator losses, projector placement, or shell bookkeeping. If those are not itemized, the chain will overstate sameness or improvement.
