/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/navier-stokes/steps/step-001/state.json:7:      "id": "exploration-001",
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-02.md:5:The attacker is mostly right about the chain's structural weakness. The original chain points at a real Navier-Stokes-versus-averaged distinction, but it spends too much of its budget on symbol-level differences before forcing the hard tests: summation, localization, prior-art calibration, and dynamic persistence.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-02.md:33:This is one of the strongest critiques. A pointwise symbol mismatch is cheap. What matters is whether the mismatch produces a sign, forbidden transfer, monotonicity, or stronger cancellation after summing admissible configurations and after localization losses are accounted for.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-02.md:45:The criticism is fair that the shortlist may privilege mechanisms that are easy to describe spectrally but weak operationally. Still, some bounded shortlist is necessary for tractability. The repair is to allow hybrid candidates and to rank them against downstream localization and dynamics, not to abandon shortlisting entirely.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-02.md:47:### 7. Step 4 introduces localization too late
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-02.md:51:This is the central structural issue. For this chain, localization is not a routine translation stage. It is one of the main filters. It needs to move earlier, before too much effort is spent on elegant but non-operative Fourier identities.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-02.md:75:Early gates are too easy to pass, while the decisive localization test arrives too late. The negative fallback is still mission-useful, but only if it is framed as a calibrated obstruction to a class of helical or triad strategies rather than a memo about a few attractive examples.
