/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md:137:**Lemma 11** (the core localization). Multiplying the NS equation by u·v_k/|u| and combining with the global energy inequality for |u|²/2, Vasseur derives a local energy inequality for v_k²/2:
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md:141:This is an *inequality* (not equality), analogous to the local energy inequality for the full solution, but restricted to the level-set region {|u| > C_k}. The last two terms are the **pressure localization terms** — Vasseur must control div(uP) and the remaining pressure term.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md:264:Vasseur shows (Appendix, Conjecture 14): **if** Proposition 3 held with β_p > 3/2, then ALL suitable weak solutions would be globally bounded (full regularity). The proof rescales u_ε(t,x) = ελu(t₀+λ²t, x₀+λx); the rescaled initial energy U_{ε,0} ~ ε^{2−5/λ}·(global energy)·λ → 0 as λ → 0 when 2β − 3 > 0 ↔ β > 3/2. So the threshold β = 3/2 is **precisely the boundary between partial and full regularity** in the De Giorgi framework. The current proof achieves β = 4/3 (limited by local pressure), which falls short.
/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/selector.md:18:   Most condition-sensitive branch. It is worth reviving only if the explicit goal is to test whether the prior geometry kill was mainly a package artifact; otherwise too much of the budget goes into auditing setup costs.
