+# Exploration 002 Report
+
+## Goal
+
+Fix the compatible solution class, theorem-hypothesis constraints, and one
+frozen localization protocol for the architecture selected in exploration-001,
+so later rewrite audits compare candidates inside the same weak-solution
+package with the same cutoff, projection, and commutator bookkeeping.
+
+## Status Log
+
+- [PROPOSED] Started report skeleton and source audit.
+- [PROPOSED] Initial working target: the local-energy flux/localization
+  architecture, provisionally focused on the localized cutoff-flux term in the
+  local energy inequality, pending confirmation from `exploration-001`.
+
+## Questions
+
+1. What is the correct solution class for this audit?
+2. What theorem-hypothesis compatibility constraints are non-negotiable?
+3. What is the first explicit circularity or package-mismatch risk?
+4. What single localization protocol is fairest for the rewrite audit?
+5. What would count later as an illegitimate mid-branch protocol change?
+
+## Source Notes
+
