+# Exploration 002 Summary
+
+- Goal: Fix the compatible weak-solution class, theorem-hypothesis
+  constraints, and one frozen localization protocol for the Step-5
+  exact-rewrite audit, working from the fallback architecture
+  `local-energy flux/localization` because `exploration-001` has not yet
+  finished.
+- What I tried: Read the Step-5 reasoning and receptionist result, then checked
+  the local architecture anchors in CKN and Vasseur, the chain/judgment
+  materials that require frozen localization and compatibility discipline, the
+  already-killed pressure and geometry branch outputs, and the meta note on
+  least-adapted localization.
+- Outcome: succeeded.
+- Key takeaway: The honest audit package is
+  `suitable weak solutions in the Leray-Hopf energy class with the local energy
+  inequality available`, tested on one fixed parabolic cylinder with one
+  standard nonnegative cutoff, and with every post-localization projection /
+  CZ / commutator cost charged in the same ledger.
+- Leads worth pursuing: Carry this exact package into Exploration 003 when the
+  gain currency and bounded rewrite family are fixed; keep the target on the
+  localized quadratic flux / nonlinear interaction term rather than drifting
+  back to far-field pressure or into geometry.
+- Unexpected findings: The most immediate honesty risk is earlier than the
+  projection/commutator issue: if the branch says `Leray-Hopf` but uses the LEI
+  cutoff balance, it has already smuggled in the `suitable weak solution`
+  package before any rewrite is tested.
+- Computations worth doing later: In the next step, write the candidate-by-
+  candidate loss ledger on this frozen package and check explicitly whether any
+  exact rewrite changes the localized balance rather than merely relocating the
+  same `1/r`, `1/r^2`, or projector/CZ burden.
+
+## Frozen Answers
+
+- Solution class: [VERIFIED/INFERRED] `suitable weak solutions` in the
+  Leray-Hopf energy class, with `p ∈ L^{3/2}_{loc}` and the local energy
+  inequality available.
+- Non-negotiable constraints: [VERIFIED/INFERRED] stay inside the LEI package,
+  use theorem inputs compatible with that pressure/energy class, and pay all
+  localization, projection, Calderon-Zygmund, and commutator costs after the
+  cutoff is inserted.
+- First circularity/package-mismatch risk: [VERIFIED/INFERRED] using the local
+  cutoff balance as though it were available for generic Leray-Hopf solutions,
+  instead of fixing the suitable-weak/LEI package at the start.
+- Frozen localization protocol: [VERIFIED/INFERRED] one Eulerian parabolic
+  cylinder `Q_r(x_*, t_*) = B_r(x_*) × (t_* - r^2, t_*)`, one standard smooth
+  nonnegative cutoff supported in `Q_r` and equal to `1` on the inner
+  half-cylinder, with `|∇φ| ~ 1/r` and `|∂_t φ| + |Δφ| ~ 1/r^2`, and one shared
+  ledger charging all post-cutoff costs to the candidate that created them.
+- Illegitimate mid-branch protocol change: [VERIFIED/INFERRED] any later move
+  that changes the solution class, swaps the single-cylinder cutoff for a more
+  adapted package, or relocates / suppresses projection-CZ-commutator costs for
+  one candidate would invalidate the fairness of the audit.
