+### Architecture Lock
+
+- [VERIFIED] The active chain requires one fixed inherited estimate
+  architecture, one named solution class, and one frozen localization protocol
+  before any candidate comparison is honest. Sources:
+  `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/CHAIN.md`,
+  `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/refined/chain-01.md`,
+  `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-01.md`
+- [VERIFIED/INFERRED] For this exploration, the honest common denominator of
+  the local record is not a Vasseur-style moving level-set package and not a
+  geometry-adapted package. It is the local energy inequality on one
+  parabolic cylinder with one standard cutoff, because that is the shared
+  localized-balance object in the CKN/Vasseur stack and the least adapted
+  package that still exposes the target nonlinear flux term. Sources:
+  `missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/ckn-1982-proof-architecture.md`,
+  `missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md`,
+  `library/meta/exploration-goal-design/when-hidden-normalization-is-a-risk-start-with-the-least-adapted-localization-that-keeps-the-scenario-visible.md`,
+  `runtime/results/codex-patlas-standalone-20260331T124016Z-receptionist-89481.md`
+
+### 1. Fixed Solution Class
+
+- [VERIFIED] CKN's localized architecture is stated for `suitable weak
+  solutions`: `u` lies in the Leray-Hopf energy class locally,
+  `p ∈ L^{3/2}_{loc}`, the equations hold distributionally, and the local
+  energy inequality holds for every nonnegative test cutoff. CKN explicitly
+  states that the LEI is what separates suitable from "mere" weak solutions.
+  Source:
+  `missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/ckn-1982-proof-architecture.md`
+- [VERIFIED] Vasseur's partial-regularity theorem also starts from `suitable
+  weak solution (u,P)` and treats the local energy inequality as part of the
+  usable package. Source:
+  `missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md`
+- [VERIFIED/INFERRED] Therefore the correct audit class is:
+  `suitable weak solutions in the Leray-Hopf energy class, with the local
+  energy inequality available`.
+  This is stricter than bare Leray-Hopf if LEI is not assumed explicitly, but
+  it is the weakest local class in the source record that actually supports the
+  localized balance being audited. Sources:
+  `missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/ckn-1982-proof-architecture.md`,
+  `missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md`,
+  `runtime/results/codex-patlas-standalone-20260331T124016Z-receptionist-89481.md`
+
+### 2. Non-Negotiable Compatibility Constraints
+
+- [VERIFIED] The architecture must stay inside a package where the local energy
+  inequality is legitimate. The chosen bad term is a cutoff-generated nonlinear
+  transport / flux term inside the LEI balance, so the audit cannot be run in a
+  class that only gives global energy control without LEI. Sources:
+  `missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/ckn-1982-proof-architecture.md`,
+  `runtime/results/codex-patlas-standalone-20260331T124016Z-receptionist-89481.md`
+- [VERIFIED] The pressure slot that enters the same localized balance is
+  `p ∈ L^{3/2}_{loc}` in the CKN package. Any theorem imported later must be
+  compatible with that pressure regularity and with a cutoff-based local
+  balance, not merely with a different fixed-scale or mild-solution norm.
+  Sources:
+  `missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/ckn-1982-proof-architecture.md`,
+  `missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/vasseur-2007-proof-architecture.md`
+- [VERIFIED] The chain record explicitly warns that mild solutions in critical
+  spaces, suitable weak solutions, local energy solutions, and other regimes do
+  not combine automatically; explicit compatibility checks are mandatory.
+  Source:
+  `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-03.md`
+- [VERIFIED] The chain also requires all candidates to survive full
+  localization, projection / Calderon-Zygmund, and commutator bookkeeping
+  inside one frozen package. Sources:
+  `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/CHAIN.md`,
+  `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/refined/chain-01.md`,
+  `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-01.md`
+
+### 3. First Explicit Circularity / Package-Mismatch Risk
+
+- [VERIFIED/INFERRED] The first explicit circularity risk is:
+  calling the class `Leray-Hopf weak solutions` while actually using the
+  `suitable weak solution` package, i.e. writing the localized cutoff balance
+  as though LEI were automatic.
+  CKN states that LEI is the extra condition separating suitable from mere weak
+  solutions, and this branch's bad term lives exactly inside that LEI balance.
+  So if LEI is not fixed at the start, the audit has already changed the
+  theorem package before any rewrite is tested. Sources:
+  `missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/ckn-1982-proof-architecture.md`,
+  `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-03.md`,
+  `runtime/results/codex-patlas-standalone-20260331T124016Z-receptionist-89481.md`
+- [VERIFIED/INFERRED] A second, downstream mismatch risk should stay visible:
+  exact projection or rewrite identities that hold before localization may
+  cease to be exact after inserting the cutoff. Those extra commutator,
+  projector, or CZ costs must be charged in the same ledger rather than treated
+  as free reformulation. Sources:
+  `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/CHAIN.md`,
+  `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-01.md`,
+  `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-01.md`
+
+### 4. Frozen Localization Protocol
+
+- [VERIFIED] CKN's local-energy localization uses one parabolic cylinder
+  `Q_r(x_*, t_*) = B_r(x_*) × (t_* - r^2, t_*)` and one standard smooth cutoff
+  `φ ∈ C_0^∞(Q_r)`, `0 ≤ φ ≤ 1`, `φ ≡ 1` on the inner half-cylinder, with
+  `|∇φ| ≤ C/r` and `|∂_t φ| + |Δφ| ≤ C/r^2`. Source:
+  `missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/ckn-1982-proof-architecture.md`
+- [VERIFIED] In that package, every candidate sees the same localization
+  balance:
+  - time-cutoff and Laplacian-cutoff terms at scale `1/r^2`,
+  - the nonlinear transport / flux term at scale `1/r`,
+  - and the pressure transport term in the same cutoff derivative slot.
+  Source:
+  `missions/navier-stokes/library-inbox/ckn-1982-proof-architecture.md`
+- [VERIFIED/INFERRED] For this audit, the fairest protocol is therefore:
+  one fixed Eulerian parabolic cylinder, one nonnegative standard cutoff, and
+  one shared ledger in which every candidate pays its own post-localization
+  costs, including projector / CZ / commutator burdens generated after the
+  cutoff is inserted.
+  This matches the refined chain's explicit fairness rule and avoids
+  candidate-specific adaptation. Sources:
+  `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/CHAIN.md`,
+  `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/refined/chain-01.md`,
+  `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/judgments/chain-01.md`,
+  `runtime/results/codex-patlas-standalone-20260331T124016Z-receptionist-89481.md`
+- [VERIFIED/INFERRED] The least-adapted-localization principle from the local
+  meta record reinforces this choice: when hidden normalization is a risk, fix
+  the package first and do not allow the observable or candidate rewrite to
+  choose a more favorable localization. Source:
+  `library/meta/exploration-goal-design/when-hidden-normalization-is-a-risk-start-with-the-least-adapted-localization-that-keeps-the-scenario-visible.md`
+
+### 5. Illegitimate Mid-Branch Protocol Changes
+
+- [VERIFIED/INFERRED] Later it would be illegitimate to:
+  move from the frozen one-cylinder cutoff package to a more adapted package
+  for only one candidate, for example by switching to Vasseur's nested level
+  sets, a geometry-adapted tube localization, a different cutoff placement, or
+  a rewrite where projection / CZ / commutator costs are charged somewhere else
+  or not charged at all.
+  That would no longer be a like-for-like audit in one weak-solution package.
+  Sources:
+  `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/CHAIN.md`,
+  `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/refined/chain-01.md`,
+  `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-003/attacks/chain-01.md`,
+  `library/meta/exploration-goal-design/when-hidden-normalization-is-a-risk-start-with-the-least-adapted-localization-that-keeps-the-scenario-visible.md`
+
+### Working Conclusion
+
+- [VERIFIED/INFERRED] The local source record supports a stable setup rather
+  than an early kill:
+  the audit can be stated honestly in one package, namely suitable weak
+  solutions in the Leray-Hopf energy class with LEI available, on one fixed
+  parabolic cylinder with one standard nonnegative cutoff and one shared
+  localization / projection / commutator ledger.
+- [VERIFIED/INFERRED] The main honesty condition is strict:
+  no later candidate may buy apparent gain by changing the solution class,
+  importing a more adapted localization, or treating post-cutoff projection
